'''Kouadio Emmanuel Boris Koné''' (born 17 May 2001) is a French professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for {{Italian football updater|Roma}} club [[AS Roma|Roma]] and the [[France national football team|France national team]].

==Early and personal life==
Koné was born in [[Colombes]], Hauts-de-Seine,<ref name="lequipe"/> and holds Ivorian and French nationalities.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fr.allafrica.com/stories/202101220275.html|title=Cote d'Ivoire: Mercato - Officiel ! Kouadio Manu Koné s'engage en faveur du Borussia Mönchengladbach|date=22 January 2021|website=allAfrica.fr}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Toulouse===
Koné made his professional debut for [[Toulouse FC|Toulouse]] in a 2–1 loss to [[Dijon FCO|Dijon]] on 24 May 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=24 May 2019|title=Dijon FCO 2–1 Toulouse FC|url=https://www.ligue1.com/ligue1/feuille_match/84983|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190524205603/https://www.ligue1.com/ligue1/feuille_match/84983|archive-date=24 May 2019|access-date=19 January 2021|website=Ligue 1}}</ref>

===Borussia Mönchengladbach===
On 21 January 2021, [[Bundesliga]] club [[Borussia Mönchengladbach]] announced the signing of Koné on a deal running until 2025, while also confirming that he would finish the [[2020–21 Toulouse FC season|2020–21]] season at Toulouse.<ref>{{Cite web|date=21 January 2021|title=Borussia sign Kouadio Koné and loan him out until the end of the season|url=https://www.borussia.de/en/news/news/2021-01-21-borussia-sign-kouadio-kone-and-loan-him-out-until-the-end-of-the-season|access-date=21 January 2021|publisher=Borussia Mönchengladbach}}</ref> The reported fee for the midfielder was €9 million.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-01-21 |title=Gladbach sign Manu Koné for €9m - Get German Football News |url=https://www.getfootballnewsgermany.com/2021/gladbach-sign-manu-kone-for-e9m/ |access-date=2024-08-19 |website=www.getfootballnewsgermany.com |language=en-US}}</ref> After completing the move in the summer, Koné was given the number 17 jersey at Mönchengladbach. Upon signing for the new club, he stated that Gladbach was desperate to get him, and at some point, he could not say no: "They tried everything, and that impressed me".<ref>{{Cite web |last=Veth |first=Manuel |title=Manu Koné: Could Leipzig Beat Out Top Clubs And Land The Gladbach Star? |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/manuelveth/2023/01/12/manu-kon-could-leipzig-beat-out-top-clubs-and-land-the-gladbach-star/ |access-date=2024-08-19 |website=Forbes |language=en}}</ref> Koné scored his first goal for Gladbach in a 5–0 [[DFB-Pokal]] win over [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] on 27 October 2021.<ref name="Soccerway" />

Koné was tied for most yellow cards in the [[2022–23 Bundesliga|2022–23]] season in the Bundesliga with Jeffrey Gouweleeuw of [[FC Augsburg]], as they both accumulated 12 bookings over the course of the league competition.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Bundesliga {{!}} Statistics 2022-2023 {{!}} Players {{!}} Yellow cards |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/stats/players/yellow-cards/2022-2023 |access-date=2024-08-19 |website=bundesliga.com - the official Bundesliga website |language=en}}</ref> Koné played a total of 30 league matches, scoring his only goal on 11 November 2022 in a 4–2 win against [[Borussia Dortmund]], as Gladbach finished the season in the 10th position.

The beginning of Koné's [[2023–24 Bundesliga|2023–24]] season was disrupted by a knee injury, suffered while being on international duty in June.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-08-01 |title=Manu Koné likely to be out until September with a knee injury - Get German Football News |url=https://www.getfootballnewsgermany.com/2023/manu-kone-likely-to-be-out-until-september-with-a-knee-injury/ |access-date=2024-08-19 |website=www.getfootballnewsgermany.com |language=en-US}}</ref> Koné once again scored his only league goal against Dortmund, this time in a 4–2 loss on 25 November 2023. He was sidelined for another month after injuring his thigh playing an international friendly match on 28 March.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Gjerulff |first=Rune |date=2024-03-28 |title=Koné ruled out for several weeks |url=https://bulinews.com/news/20880/kone-ruled-out-for-several-weeks |access-date=2024-08-19 |website=Bundesliga News in English |language=en}}</ref>

===Roma===
On 30 August 2024, Koné moved to Italy, and joined [[Serie A]] club [[AS Roma|Roma]] for an €18 million estimated fee, signing a five-year contract. The deal was structured as a loan for the 2024–25 season, followed by an obligation to buy.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.asroma.com/en/news/71769/manu-kone-is-a-new-giallorossi-player|title=Manu Kone is a new giallorossi player|publisher=[[AS Roma|Roma]]|date=30 August 2024|accessdate=30 August 2024}}</ref> Koné made his debut for the ''Gialorossi'' two days later, on 1 September, as a substitute in the 0–0 draw against Juventus. He made his first start for his new team on 15 September in a 1–1 draw against Genoa. On 27 October, he scored his first goal for Roma in a 5–1 loss against [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]] in the Serie A.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-10-27 |title=Serie A {{!}} Fiorentina 5-1 Roma: Viola destroy sorry Giallorossi |url=https://football-italia.net/serie-a-fiorentina-5-1-roma-viola-destroy/ |access-date=2025-06-06 |website=football-italia.net |language=en-GB}}</ref>

Koné quickly established himself as an indispensable figure in Roma's midfield, with particularly notable performances in the [[UEFA Europa League]], where he delivered standout displays, such as in the 3–0 victory over [[S.C. Braga|SC Braga]] on 12 December, where he registered an assist, made 7 key passes, and completed 46 out of 51 passes.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-12-13 |title=The numbers behind Manu Koné's stellar performance vs SC Braga |url=https://romapress.net/the-numbers-behind-manu-kones-stellar-performance-vs-sc-braga/ |access-date=2025-06-06 |website=romapress.net |language=en-US}}</ref> After Roma finished fifth in the Serie A for the 2024–25 season, after a late surge under new manager [[Claudio Ranieri]], Koné described the season as "complicated", lamenting the fact that the club changed three coaches during the season: [[Daniele De Rossi]], [[Ivan Jurić]] and [[Claudio Ranieri|Ranieri]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-06-02 |title=Manu Kone on his first season at Roma: "It was complicated." |url=https://romapress.net/manu-kone-on-his-first-season-at-roma-it-was-complicated-we-were-lucky-to-have-ranieri/ |access-date=2025-06-06 |website=romapress.net |language=en-US}}</ref>

== International career ==
Koné represented France as a youth international, competing at the [[France national under-18 football team|U18]], [[France national under-19 football team|U19]] and [[France national under-21 football team|U21]] level.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Kouadio Koné|url=https://www.fff.fr/equipe-nationale/joueur/9448-kone-kouadio/fiche.html|access-date=10 March 2021|website=FFF|language=fr}}</ref> Koné was also a member of France's team at the [[2024 Summer Olympics]], winning a silver medal after losing 5–3 in the final against Spain.

Koné made his debut for the senior [[France national football team|France national team]] on 6 September 2024 in a [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League A|Nations League]] game against Italy at the [[Parc des Princes]]. He substituted [[Youssouf Fofana (French footballer)|Youssouf Fofana]] in the 58th minute of a 3–1 loss for France.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=ESPN|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/698898/italy-france|title=France v Italy game report|date=6 September 2024}}</ref>

